The paper proposes a method to enhance learning models with world knowledge in the form of Knowledge Graph (KG) fact triples for Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves deep learning models, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. The use of attention mechanism and convolution-based model suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. The paper also deals with knowledge representation and retrieval, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) categories.
